652849e5-92cc-58c9-bf70-a5a4f6baff5c,tg:rubgr:2812,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"

With Bruegel's landscape engravings, not so much the drawings which are reversed, but a composition like 'insidiosus auceps' - different datings suggested - (Bast. 10 or Bast. 18) taken from high looking down on the Valley & behind with the huge mountains [...] cf. Leonardo drawing c. 1503. Landscape with Storm in the Alps, Windsor, Clark, Leonardo, pl. 37, (probable R.A. Exh.) N° 199, Windsor, N° 12409, Goldscheider, pl.108. The Windsor drawings were owned by Francesco Melzi, who died in 1570.

column4: <content>With Bruegel's landscape engravings, not so much the drawings which are reversed, but a composition like 'insidiosus auceps'  - different datings suggested - (Bast. 10 or Bast. 18) taken from high looking down on the Valley & behind with the huge mountains [...] cf. Leonardo drawing c. 1503. Landscape with Storm in the Alps, Windsor, Clark, Leonardo, pl. 37, (probable R.A. Exh.) N° 199, Windsor, N° 12409, Goldscheider, pl.108. The Windsor drawings were owned by Francesco Melzi, who died in 1570.</content>
